items.title: Awesome Elixir
items.content_text:
### Applications

*   [Tai (‚≠ê476)](https://github.com/fremantle-capital/tai) - A composable, real time, cryptocurrency market data and trade execution toolkit.
*   [workbench (‚≠ê120)](https://github.com/fremantle-industries/workbench) - From Idea to Execution - Manage your trading operation across a globally distributed cluster.

### Authentication

*   [elixir\_auth\_google (‚≠ê280)](https://github.com/dwyl/elixir-auth-google) - The simplest way to add Google OAuth authentication ("Sign in with Google") to your Elixir/Phoenix app.

### Email

*   [swoosh (‚≠ê1.5k)](https://github.com/swoosh/swoosh) - Compose, deliver and test your Emails (with attachments!) easily in Elixir with adapters for SMTP, Sendgrid, Mandrill, Mailgun, Postmark and lots others, plus Phoenix integration with mailbox preview.

### Framework Components

*   [recaptcha (‚≠ê113)](https://github.com/samueljseay/recaptcha) - A simple reCaptcha 2 library for Elixir applications.

### Instrumenting / Monitoring

*   [wobserver (‚≠ê926)](https://github.com/shinyscorpion/wobserver) - Web based metrics, monitoring, and observer.

### Lexical analysis

*   [abnf\_parsec (‚≠ê55)](https://github.com/princemaple/abnf_parsec) - ABNF in and parser out.

### Macros

*   [pathex (‚≠ê356)](https://github.com/hissssst/pathex) - Zero-dependency, blazing fast functional lenses.

### Networking

*   [hades (‚≠ê27)](https://github.com/fklement/hades) - A wrapper for NMAP written in Elixir.

### ORM and Datamapping

*   [barrel\_ex (‚≠ê0)](https://github.com/jxub/barrel_ex) - [Barrel-db](https://barrel-db.org/) distributed document-oriented database REST client in Elixir.

### PDF

*   [chromic\_pdf (‚≠ê456)](https://github.com/bitcrowd/chromic_pdf) - A client for Chrome's DevTools API to generate PDFs (HTML to PDF).
*   [pdf\_generator (‚≠ê343)](https://github.com/gutschilla/elixir-pdf-generator) - A simple wrapper for wkhtmltopdf or puppeteer (HTML to PDF) for use in Elixir projects.
*   [puppeteer\_pdf (‚≠ê100)](https://github.com/coletiv/puppeteer-pdf) - Another wrapper around puppeteer (HTML to PDF) for use in Elixir projects.

### Queue

*   [flume (‚≠ê79)](https://github.com/scripbox/flume) - A blazing fast job processing system backed by GenStage & Redis.

items.title: Awesome Python Typing
items.content_text:
### Articles / PEPs

*   [PEP-3107](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3107) - Function Annotations.
*   [PEP-482](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0482/) - Literature Overview for Type Hints.
*   [PEP-483](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0483/) - The Theory of Type Hints.
*   [PEP-484](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0484/) - Type Hints.
*   [PEP-526](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0526/) - Syntax for Variable Annotations.
*   [PEP-544](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0544/) - Protocols: Structural subtyping (static duck typing).
*   [PEP-557](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0557/) - Data Classes.
*   [PEP-560](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0560/) - Core support for typing module and generic types.
*   [PEP-561](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0561/) - Distributing and Packaging Type Information.
*   [PEP-563](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0563/) - Postponed Evaluation of Annotations.
*   [PEP-585](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0585/) - Type Hinting Generics In Standard Collections.
*   [PEP-586](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0586/) - Literal Types.
*   [PEP-589](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0589/) - TypedDict: Type Hints for Dictionaries with a Fixed Set of Keys.
*   [PEP-591](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0591/) - Adding a final qualifier to typing.
*   [PEP-593](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0593/) - Flexible function and variable annotations.
*   [PEP-604](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0604/) - Complementary syntax for Union\[].
*   [PEP-612](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0612/) - Parameter Specification Variables.
*   [PEP-613](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0613/) - Explicit Type Aliases.
